By definition of polynomial evaluation:

`eval (q : ℂ) (X - C lamb)` = `(q : ℂ) - (lamb : ℂ)`

So, `‖eval (↑q) (X - C lamb)‖` = `‖(q : ℂ) - (lamb : ℂ)‖`

The norm of a complex number `z = x + iy` is `√(x² + y²)`, which is always ≥ 0.

In Lean, for any complex number `z`, `‖z‖` (which is `Complex.abs z`) satisfies `0 ≤ ‖z‖`.

Therefore, the goal `0 ≤ ‖eval (↑q) (X - C lamb)‖` is true by definition of complex norm.

